Implement program philosophy and strategies consistent with guidelines established by Head Coach;
Assist head coach in promoting program within the District, community and media;
Assist head coach in providing written rules/expectations to student athletes and their parents and enforce these fairly among all participants;
Be knowledgeable of and enforce school, District, AIA and/or league rules, regulations, procedures and policies;
Direct supervision of student athletes in practice areas, locker rooms, buses and at all times on away trips;
Assist head coach in organizing and conducting practices during the regulated season;
Assist head coach in making recommendations regarding scheduling;
Assist head coach in preparing team for competition;
Assist head coach in developing and implementing an effective scouting program;
Assume head coaching responsibilities in the absence of the head coach;
Attend staff meetings;
Assist in care and maintenance of equipment and facilities;
Work with Athletic Director in matters concerning the program;
Serve as a positive role model for student athletes;
Promote good sportsmanship;
Enforce all AIA bylaws and regulations;
Perform other tasks as assigned by the Head Coach or Athletic Director.

KNOWLEDGE AND SKILLS REQUIRED:
Knowledge of sport.
Knowledge of AIA bylaws and regulations.
Knowledge of district policies and procedures concerning athletics.
Skill in motivating student athletes.
Skill in communicating with student athletes, parents, and coaches.
Skill in organization and planning.

